@NODE sections "Window Sections"

  @{i}ADoom Path@{ui}
  This has a button and a string gadget.  The Button lets you select the path of the
  ADoom executable using a Reqtools load requester.  The path is then put into the
  string gadget.

  @{i}External Wad File@{ui}
  This has a button, a string gadget and a checkbox.  The button lets you select
  which external wad file you wish to use using a Reqtools load requester and the
  path is then put into the string gadget.  This entire section can be turned off
  by using the checkbox

  @{i}Controller@{ui}
  This section has a button and a string.  The button brings up another window which
  has 4 buttons each with the the type of controller you can use.  The controller
  you select will be put in the string gadget.	You can also type the controller
  you want in the string gadget.

  @{i}Screenmode@{ui}
  This has a button, a string and 2 integer gadgets.  The button brings up a Reqtools
  screenmode requester and whatever you select the screenmode id, width and heights
  are put in the conrresponding string and integer gadgets.  To set the id you
  can Edit it yourself in the id string.  To set the width you can edit it yourself
  with the width integer.  To set the height you can edit it yourself with the height
  integer.

  @{i}Sound@{ui}
  This has 2 checkboxes.  One turns on the sound and one turns on the music.

  @{i}Automap@{ui}
  This has 2 checkboxes.  One turns off the map background and one makes the map
  rotate.

  @{i}Misc@{ui}
  This has a checkbox for turning on the doom demo, a button and a string to select
  the processor type.  The button opens up another window with 6 buttons with
  the normal 68k processor types.  The type you choose is then put into the string.

  @{i}DeHackEd@{ui}
  This has a button, a string and a checkbox.  The button lets you select a DeHackEd
  file using a Reqtools load requester which is then put in the string.  You can
  turn off this section with the checkbox.

@ENDNODE

@NODE menus "Menus"

  @{b}Project@{ub}

    @{i}Save@{ui}
    Saves all changes to the options into the settings file.  These options will be loaded
    upon startup of the program again.

    @{i}Save As@{ui}
    Save all the current options into a external settings file using a Reqtools save requester.

    @{i}Load@{ui}
    Allows you to select an external settings file to load into the GUI.

    @{i}Iconify@{ui}
    Turns the window into a icon which is placed on the desktop at the position and image
    selected.

    @{i}Information@{ui}
    If the program is unregistered it brings up how to register and the address of where
    to register to.  If the program is registered it brings up the person it is registered
    to.

    @{i}About@{ui}
    Description of the program and the people responsable for it.

    @{i}Quit@{ui}
    Quits the program completely

  @{b}GUI@{ub}

    @{i}Window Title@{ui}
    Opens a Reqtools string requester in which you can set the title of the window.

    @{i}Font@{ui}
    Opens a Reqtools Font requester in which you can set the font of the window.

    @{i}Colours@{ui}
    Opens a window with 3 buttons and a frame.	When you press 'Select' buttons
    if opens a Reqtools palette requester in which the colour you select is put
    in the frame.  If you select 'Cancel' any changes will be ignored.  If you
    'Use' any changes will be applied.

    @{b}Appicon@{ub}
      @{i}Image@{ui}
      This opens a Reqtools load requester which lets you select any icon to set
      as the appicon image.

      @{i}Text@{ui}
      This opens a Reqtools string requester which lets you set the text underneath
      the appicon.

      @{i}Position@{ui}
      Opens a window which lets you set the x and y coordinates of the icon on the
      desktop.	Simply move the window the position you require and hit the snap
      button.

    @{i}Save Prefs@{ui}
    Saves all changes the GUI preferences file.

    @{i}Save Prefs As@{ui}
    Saves all changes into a external preferences file which you can select with the
    Reqtools Save file requester.

    @{i}Load Prefs@{ui}
    Lets you load an external preferences file using a Reqtools Load requester.

@ENDNODE

@NODE registration "Registration Requester"

  This a simple window that you cannot close without a registation code which
  is supplied by White Star Software.  This has 3 string gadgets in which you
  are supposed to put your name and address and then your registration code.

  After this you don't get the requester upon startup and you dont get the
  registration requester anymore.

@ENDNODE

